---
---

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid fade">
      <div>
        <p class="section-label">The name</p>
        <h2>What's a feedthrough?</h2>
        <p class="body">
          In vacuum systems, a <strong>feedthrough</strong> is a component that passes signals
          in and out of a sealed chamber without breaking the vacuum. You can't reach inside
          directly — but the feedthrough lets you observe and control what's happening in there
          anyway.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          The parallel is exact. Feedthrough extracts runtime debug data from inside a running
          web app without disturbing it, and sends control signals back in — clicks, keystrokes,
          DOM queries — without breaking the execution environment.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="diagram">
        <div class="layer">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Vacuum Chamber</div>
            <ul class="card-items">
              <li>experiment running</li>
              <li>signals generated</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="conn">
            <span class="line"></span>
            <span class="conn-label">feedthrough</span>
            <span class="line"></span>
            <span class="head"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint">instruments outside</div>
        </div>

        <div class="layer">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Your Web App</div>
            <ul class="card-items">
              <li>React state changing</li>
              <li>fetches firing</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="conn">
            <span class="line"></span>
            <span class="conn-label">@feedthrough/core</span>
            <span class="line"></span>
            <span class="head"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint">your AI agent</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .body { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .body strong { color: var(--text); }

  .diagram {
    background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px 24px;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 28px;
  }
  .layer { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; width: 100%; }

  .card {
    background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px 20px;
    width: 100%; max-width: 260px; text-align: center;
  }
  .card-title {
    font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .card-items { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .card-items li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .conn { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin: 4px 0 0; }
  .line { width: 1px; height: 14px; background: var(--text-dim); }
  .conn-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--green);
    padding: 4px 0;
  }
  .head {
    width: 0; height: 0;
    border-left: 4px solid transparent; border-right: 4px solid transparent;
    border-top: 5px solid var(--text-dim);
    margin-top: -1px;
  }

  .endpoint {
    font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }
</style>
